14/11/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- In an interview for Voice of America on Thursday (13 November), outgoing NATO Secretary General Lord George Robertson described Macedonia as one of history's Balkan success stories. Despite difficulties, the country managed to find the best way to deal with its challenges, said Robertson, praising the work of the current multiethnic coalition government and implementation of the Ohrid Peace Accord. (Utrinski Vesnik - 14/11/03; MIA - 13/11/03)
